Product Line Manager 
Micronâ€™s Embedded Business Unit (EBU) is looking for a Product Line Manager for NAND components product line. You will play a key role in enabling NAND products for the key segments such as automotive, industrial, and consumer. You will be critical in defining product roadmaps, innovating for best-in-class products, and working with cross-functional teams to deliver the product. 
Key Responsibilities 
Develop and implement go-to-market plans for new products
 Identify gaps and implement changes in the product lines to profitably increase revenue and market share for existing products. 
Support customers and sales team with product collateral 
Monitor design win progress in key segments/accounts 
Develop pricing strategy for product lines 
Tactical activities may include working closely with engineering on product features and timelines, leading cost reduction activities, working on product change notifications, supporting supply escalations, and responding to requests from customers and internal partners within the business unit 
Requirements 
8+ years of experience in Product Marketing and product line management in driving strategy to execution through programs, leadership, and innovation 
Strong background and understanding of NAND Flash, experience in managed NAND/SSD a plus 
Bachelorâ€™s or Master's degree in Business, Marketing, or Engineering 
Ability to work in fast paced/changing environment, strong organization skills to prioritize projects based on ROI 
Automotive experience desirable 
Strong communication and presentation skills 
A record of performance excellence for the current area of responsibility 
This position may require some travel to customer and non-customer sites worldwide 
